'''[[Cook Islands]]''' competed at the [[2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]] held in [[Ashgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]] from September 17 to 27. 10 athletes competed in 4 different sports. Cook Islands team couldn't receive any medal at the Games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ashgabat2017.com/results/cok|title=Cook Islands {{!}} The 5th Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=ashgabat2017.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref>
Cook Islands also made its first appearance at an [[Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]] event during the Games along with other [[Oceania]] nations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cookislandsnews.com/item/65618-cooks-debut-in-asian-indoor-games/65618-cooks-debut-in-asian-indoor-games|title=Cooks debut in Asian Indoor Games|last=Kumar|first=Rashneel|access-date=2017-10-11|language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ocasia.org/Game/GameParticular.aspx?9QoyD9QEWPdkzAjI/K7uyA==|title=Olympic Council of Asia : Games|website=www.ocasia.org|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2017/sep/17/repression-raids-sport-turkmenistan-asian-games-tyranny|title=IOC turns a blind eye to Turkmenistan using sport to legitimise tyranny {{!}} Kieran Pender|last=Pender|first=Kieran|date=2017-09-17|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-10-11|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>
