'''Skonto Hall''' (also Skonto Arena) is an [[arena]] in [[Riga]], [[Latvia]]. It is primarily used for different exhibitions.  Skonto Hall holds 6,500 people and was renovated in 2006, so that it could be used as one of the venues for the [[2006 Men's World Ice Hockey Championships]]. The hall also played host to the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2003]]. It is immediately adjacent to [[Skonto Stadium]]. 

